Might as well take the Flag Down.<br><br>
It's a Wonderful Life, we live, But somebody has to pay the price. If we took what you believe then the jokers in Washington during the 60's were right. They also found ways of keeping theirs sons out of the war but who will defend your right to bare arms?<br><br>
You say we should have left the Vietnamese to defend themselves. So, why interveen in Kuwait. <br>
We should have left Saddam Hussein do as he pleases, McVeigh, to do as he pleases and Charles Manson. And we should not get involved with providing police service to victims of crime.<br>
Why get involved, It's a wonderful life and I want to live it, but you say let others spill their blood.<br><br>
So, why lift up your country's flag if your neighbor takes offense to its presence. Do you suggest we take it down and live in peace? <br><br>
Silence and failure to act is the first step toward war.<br><br>
There was a &quot;doc,&quot; a Corpsmen assigned to our platoon and while I have the highest respect and give corpsmen great honor, this corpsmen though of himself and only himself. <br><br>
&quot;Doc,&quot;  he shared your views about the war. <br><br>
After all he was drafted and certainly did not volunteer for combat duty. He was willing to serve but from a distance that why he joined the Navy. <br><br>
That corpsmen would puke and get sick as soon as we went out the perimeter wire and we would have to come back and have someone else take his place. <br><br>
During a major battle on the 21St of November 1967 after another corpsmen had tagged me to be medivacked, that corpsmen fearing that we were going to be overrun hustled into a little hole and shot himself in the leg. He then medivacked himself out taking my place on the last chopper out that night. <br><br>
You know, although I was hurt and was just as scared as he was, I was glad he was gone, his fear could have been contagious and the battle was still going on. <br><br>
Many in Nam caused their own self inflicted wounds and today they hide and feel that shame. They justify their cowardliness by demonstrating and speaking out against a just war, but I say let them put little roses in the barrel of their weapons but do not demonstrate against those willing to defend our country and the American way of life.<br><br>
Yes, we've learned a lot from Vietnam and the main lesson is how to make causalities out of American heros who did fight and who did as their country told them to.<br><br>

